<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2925] CMake build does not work with OpenSSL nor anything installed in non-system location</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2925</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s caused by many incorrect CMake variable names.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples of correct variable names:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;LIBEVENT_INCLUDE_DIRS&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;OPENSSL_INCLUDE_DIR (without S !!)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Boost_INCLUDE_DIRS (not BOOST !!)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It is almost funny how these variable names are inconsistent, nonetheless correct names should be used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
